JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) &ndash; JSE-listed Wesizwe Platinum has appointed Feng Tao as FD, effective July 1. Tao, who holds an MBA from the Schulich School of Business, York University, in the US, and a Bachelor of Law degree from Jilin University, Changchun, in China, will fill the vacancy as a result of the resignation of Wenliang Ma in September 2016. Tao has more than 15 years&rsquo; experience as an FD, a CFO and a board member in various companies, including at companies listed on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange. He is an expert in project finance, portfolio management and legal affairs.